<BaseLayout lang="en" title="About | Openfilm" description="About Openfilm blog" alternatePath="/zh/about/">
  <section class="about-grid">
    <article class="about-card">
      <p class="kicker">About Openfilm</p>
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>
        Openfilm is an independent blog about film photography, camera tools, darkroom craft,
        and visual culture. It cares about more than gear specs: it asks how images are kept,
        viewed, exchanged, and why analog photography still matters.
      </p>
      <p>
        The writing connects film stocks, shooting methods, processing variables, and image
        communities so readers can find both practical guidance and the cultural reasons behind the practice.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="about-aside">
      <p class="kicker">Editorial focus</p>
      <p>Film stock / Camera desk / Darkroom / Culture</p>
      <p>Start with a roll of film, then move into the materials, tools, and ways of seeing around it.</p>
    </aside>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
